%META:TOPICPARENT{name="WebHome"}%
---+ Troubleshooting

%TOC%

---++ The scene stays black or the loading card never clears

   * Check the browser console for a CORS or 404 on =geometry_data/CaloGeometry.glb.gz=.
   * WebGL2 must be available. Visit =chrome://gpu= (Chromium) or =about:support= (Firefox) and look for =WebGL 2 Enabled=.
   * Some corporate proxies strip the =Content-Encoding: gzip= header; request an exemption for the deployment URL.

---++ Live mode shows "waiting for events"

   * Verify outbound HTTPS to =atlas-live.cern.ch= (proxy / VPN).
   * Open dev-tools → Network and look for 401, 403 or a CORS preflight failure.
   * Use the =⏸= / =▶= controls to reset the long-poll without reloading the page.
   * Fall back to the [[DataModes][Samples]] mode to confirm the rendering pipeline is healthy.

---++ Cells look duplicated or flicker

Usually two overlapping geometries. Open the [[Geometry][ATLAS Ghost]]
panel and turn off any envelope you do not need; the Tile barrel envelope
and the Tile active cells share a boundary and can z-fight at very wide
zoom levels.

---++ Energy bars are all saturated red

The palette ceiling is too low, or a stray high-energy cell compressed the
dynamic range. Two fixes:

   * Raise the sub-detector's =max= slider (or type a numeric value in the slider's text input).
   * Double-click the slider to re-sample the 97th percentile.

---++ A run's first event arrives and then nothing

The ATLAS Live feed back-pressure is handled by ATLANTIS: if the feed is
saturated, live mode buffers and then replays. Pause with =⏸= for a
minute; resume with =▶=.

---++ Local mode rejects a file

   * The file must be JiveXML — not an xAOD, D3PD or ROOT file. See [[DataModes][Data Modes]] for the accepted formats.
   * A =.gz= file is auto-decoded; other compressions are not.
   * For multi-event XMLs, the =Event= tags must each have =runNumber= and =eventNumber= attributes.

---++ Opening an issue

If none of the above applies, open an issue at
[[https://github.com/nipscern/cgv-web/issues][github.com/nipscern/cgv-web/issues]]
with:

   * Browser name and version.
   * The failing event (if small enough) or its run / event number.
   * The full console log (right-click → =Save as…=).
   * A screenshot of the error state — =P= while the overlay is up works.

